  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;Title&gt;My daughter's skin condition (2yrs old)&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Gaff&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;During 2018 my daughter started to get painful rashes on her body, mainly around the inside of her elbows and knees but also on her arms and legs. It looked like eczema and it seemed to come and go but we took her to our GP and were prescribed creams and on one occasion some steroid cream.  
Her skin would get a little better but never cleared up. In early 2019 her skin got much worse with rashes covering most of her body and her constantly complaining she is itchy. She will regularly scratch herself until she bleeds and wakes up several times every night.  
We returned to our GP many times, each time given different creams to try. None of them worked so on 3rd May we asked to be referred to a dermatologist. It is now July and we still have no appointment. We chased it up last week and we were told that we shouldn't expect an appointment before the end of August.  
I can't believe that a 2 year old child has to suffer for this amount of time. We even looked into a private consultant but the costs are too high for us.  
We are in the Manchester area and have been referred to the unit at Salford.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
